comentarios.content: First Episode Review: *Spoilers for the first episode.* Truly beautiful, this first episode felt like a movie. The boy was an amazing character, and we didn't even know his name. The animation was really good and it had a soundtrack like a ghibli movie. To your eternity is definitely going to be one of the best of the season. Basing off of this first episode it seems extremely well written, The boy's struggle of being alone consoling in his pet wolf was truly beautiful. The concept itself is extremely interesting I have never seen an anime, with such a strange concept that works so well.

First of all, sorry for my bad english- (I JUST WATCHED EPISODE 1 WITHOUT READING MANGA). I'm just going to say that i was hyped as f*** since the series score was so high in the web, and well, yeah it was ok, but not that much.
